Text.Value: Link to Lae'zel's parasite, show her Vlaakith's mind.
Poisoned by a life of propaganda. I pity you, Lae'zel.
And I pity your faithless mind.
Who in the Hells are you?
Glorious Vlaakith. I am unclean. I exhort you, grant me guidance.
*Lae'zel believes a zaith'isk device cleanses the parasite - but it's used for extracting memories and killing the infected.*
One promise. One drop in the Astral Sea.
Mother Gith's son lives, caged by a prison of your design. Our people deserve the truth - but you have denied it to us.
Go on, then. Kneel before Vlaakith.
The betrayer Voss LIES!

Do not fail me. For you would not survive the flood to follow.
Use the tadpole. Seek Vlaakith's mind through her psionic conveyance.
Queen Vlaakith - tsk'va!

Text.Value: Vlaakith hid Mother Gith's son from us. Reject her - we've found a new path to follow.
Face the facts, Lae'zel. Vlaakith lied to your people. It's time you reject your queen.
Voss was right, Vlaakith is our slaver. Denounce her - we must walk free.
Voss was right, Vlaakith is your slaver. Denounce her - you must walk free.
The traitor Voss has lied to you. The Heretic Prince would shatter us in an instant. The Great Dominion, shrunk to the head of a pin.
OUT.

Text.Value: Kneel, Lae'zel. To be the god-queen's Chosen is an extraordinary honour.
I will consume you. I will unmake you!

Out of my head - the Queen has spoken!
*Vlaakith does not welcome her finest young warriors into her royal city to reward them, but to consume their essence in her quest for godhood.*
Raise your eyes. Look upon She Who Conquers.

Text.Value: Venerable Vlaakith. Please, I beg you to listen. I seek -
I am Vlaakith. Undying Queen of the noble githyanki. God Regent of the Six Arms of Tu'narath.

EditorData.NodeContext: anger should build rhythmically here, each consonant semi-spat in rage

Text.Value: Orpheus will live, and I will hear his creed. This is my word.
Vlaakith tavki na'zin. I am truth.
Shka'keth! You speak against the Eternal Queen?
*In this endless sea of understanding, you find truth.*
Link to Lae'zel's parasite. Show her Vlaakith's mind.
The Heretic Prince would shatter us in an instant. The Great Dominion, shrunk to the head of a pin.

*In this endless sea of understanding, you find truth. There is no cleansing, no ascension, no Chosen. Vlaakith will take Lae'zel's life essence for herself.*

Text.Value: No. It can't be. I believed you - I believed everything.

Text.Value: Queen Vlaakith - tsk'va!
Connect with Lae'zel's parasite. 'Commander of Dragons. This is your destiny.'
I've seen the captive Orpheus with my own eyes, spoken to Jhe'stil Kith'rak Voss. You lied to us, enslaved us.
Your word is nothing. You are nothing.
Keep silent.
Return to the Astral Prism. Slay Orpheus the pretender.
So the worm bows to the wyvern. Have some dignity, stand up to Vlaakith!
You are Hshar'lak. And still you speak my name.
Out of my head!
I named you Hshar'lak. Yet you still call me Queen.
Hear my words, vin'iisk.
And you - you are abominations twice over. You carry ghaik parasites. And you harbour the Heretic Prince Orpheus.
I have my dignity. What I do not have is patience for your disloyalty.
I will not entertain madness. Only in Vlaakith's might am I free!
Go on, Lae'zel. Kneel before our queen.
Go on, Lae'zel. Kneel before your god-queen.
*Can this be true? Is the githyanki prince really a threat to his own people or simply a challenge to Vlaakith's rule?*
My forgiveness. Yes, I know - and I might yet grant it.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lae'zel rises and the hologram flickers away

Text.Value: We are githyanki. We move mountains, we snuff out stars, we shake the planes.
A final chance. Kneel before me. Make your promise.
Stand your ground. Don't fall for Vlaakith's lies.
Return to the Astral Prism. Slay Orpheus the pretender.
Ch'mar, zal'a Vlaakith. Your grace is my honour. Orpheus will die by my hand - and I will take my rightful place at your side.

EditorData.NodeContext: cheh-MAR ZAL-ah VLAH-kith. Vlaakith's will above all

Text.Value: Baht t'Vlaakith. No githyanki's held the honour. My faith, almost lost to the dark winds -
The kith'raki will bring you. I will tear your flesh from your bones and devour your skull's marrow while you beg for death.
Damned fool. The wretched cannot sway the divine!
The Mistress of Castle Susurrus does not require invitation.
No. I have not cast off my chains only to be rebound.
You carry a ghaik parasite. You harbour the Heretic Prince. Yet so blind is your faith that you still call me Queen.
Serve me and I will ascend you. You will be no mere warrior, nor kith'rak. You will be Baht t'Vlaakith.
Look upon the figure with reverence.
How incredible, for them to carry it back.
There's little time. I will speak, and you will listen.
Kneel before me. Make your promise.
*Lae'zel's mind reels with images of Vlaakith, the Prism, and the githyanki prince inside it.*
I have only a moment. And you, Hshar'lak, will listen.
The Undying Queen. Honour be!
*Water and blood. They envelop you, they drag you downward. You are submerged in past, present, and future.*

Text.Value: Keep silent.
I gave you my faith, and you called me traitor. I gave you my life, and you ordered your knights to hunt me.
Vin'iisk. I am your Queen! Would you not bend in my honour?
*Lae'zel's thoughts become yours. The sight of Orpheus looms over her mind; Voss' words echo within it. She means to forever turn her back on Vlaakith.*
Commander of Dragons. My only, my Chosen.
She - she has good reason, surely. Vlaakith is my faith, my - my very purpose.

Synopsis: Vlaakith offers a last chance for Laezel to do her bidding and kill Orpheus, promising ascension. Player can suggest things, but not sure if it's going to have any long term impact.
